Exactly two weeks after the teaser artwork was posted on social media, Nigerian Afro-pop singer Davido and U.S hip-pop singer, Chris Brown finally release the much-anticipated song, “Blow My Mind”. And the song is indeed mind-blowing.    A post shared by  Davido Adeleke (@davidoofficial) on Jul 25, 2019 at 11:36pm PDT  “Blow My Mind” is the first collaboration between Davido and Chris Brown. However, this is not the first time that Brown would collaborate with a Nigerian artiste. Brown and Wizkid had collaborated on “African Bad Gyal” in 2017. Brown is an award-winning singer and actor who has sold over 100 million records worldwide, making him one of the world’s best-selling music artists. Throughout his career, Brown has won several awards, including a Grammy Award, 15 BET Awards, four Billboard Music Awards, and six Soul Train Music Awards. Davido, the 2018 BET’s Best International Act also has a number of other international collaborations to his credit like “Pere” Rae Sremmurd & Young Thug, “Swing” by Quavo and also featuring Normani, Tinashe’s “How Long”, Clean Bandit’s “Beautiful” among other songs. Listen: 